Russian Equity Movers: Rosneft, Sberbank, VTB Group Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-19T15:32:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/russian-equity-movers-rosneft-sberbank-vtb-group-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  slid 1
percent to 1,438.74 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow, paring
earlier losses of as much as 4.5 percent. The dollar-denominated
RTS Index lost 0.6 percent to 1,575.33.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX),  Russia ’s largest oil producer, sank
to its lowest in more than a week as crude tumbled below $80 a
barrel in  New York . The shares fell 2.2 percent to 199.08
rubles, the lowest since Aug. 11. The stock pared earlier losses
of as much as 5.7 percent.  OAO Sberbank (SBER RX), Russia’s biggest lender, dropped to
the lowest in a year as banks worldwide retreated on fears the
debt crisis may cause funding problems. The shares slid 3.4
percent to 78.83 rubles, the lowest level since August last
year.  VTB Group (VTBR RX), the country’s second-biggest bank,
headed for its lowest close since December. Its shares dropped
as much as 6.7 percent before closing 0.2 percent lower at 6.8
kopecks.  To contact the reporter on this story:
